      "id": "CVE-2026-22738",
      "publishedDate": "2026-03-27T05:21:07.168Z",
      "lastModifiedDate": "2026-03-28T03:55:47.438Z",
      "description": "In Spring AI, a SpEL injection vulnerability exists in SimpleVectorStore when a user-supplied value is used as a filter expression key. A malicious actor could exploit this to execute arbitrary code. Only applications that use SimpleVectorStore and pass user-supplied input as a filter expression key are affected.\nThis issue affects Spring AI: from 1.0.0 before 1.0.5, from 1.1.0 before 1.1.4.",
      "severity": 9.8,
      "references": [
        {
          "url": "https://spring.io/security/cve-2026-22738",
          "type": "reference"
        }
      ],
      "affected": [
